<br>
There are a lot of &quot;if's&quot;.  <br>
<br>
IF.. he spent &quot;raid points&quot;, it belongs to him. (period)<br>
<br>
IF.. the guild considered the BoC as guild property, NO ONE should have had to spend points. (period)<br>
<br>
Can you see the distinction?  The difference is that he HAD TO spend points to get to sword.  Therefore, it became his.<br>
<br>
At this point, the entire topic is mute.  We will never know the &quot;whole-truth&quot;.  <br>
<br>
ANY guild, raid or group that USES a system that costs a player chances at OTHER gear, in order to obtain a different piece, is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>wrong</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to consider ANY SUCH GEAR guild property.<br>
<br>
Just to over simplify things... lets look at a kael raid (ironic :P ).<br>
<br>
A mob drops a BP for thurg quest.  A cleric and warrior both need it.  <br>
<br>
The warrior has 6 &quot;points&quot; saved up (because he passed on roll for arms/legs/boots/helm) from prior raids.<br>
<br>
The Cleric has 5 &quot;points&quot; saved up (because he spent a point on legs) from prior raids.<br>
<br>
The warrior wins because he had more points.  BECAUSE he gave up on OTHER gear, in order to get a better chance at a BP.<br>
<br>
Thats my point.  Pure and simple. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198804">Impudent Blasphemy</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
